## Design for your audience
<p>When designing your component or pattern, you should analyse your users’ choice of:</p>
<ul>
<li>operating systems</li>
<li>browsers</li>
<li>browser versions</li>
<li>screen size/resolutions</li>
<li>choice of mobile device</li>
</ul>
<p>If evidence shows that your users have specific needs or extra support requirements, you can use this to make a case for not meeting these browser requirements.</p>
<p>For example, components and patterns used exclusively in products that internal teams use may not need to be tailored to work on smaller viewports, as it is likely that these users will only be using the product on a desktop browser.</p>
